Task D — Consume the SSE stream
Response is Content-Type: text/event-stream. Each event is data: <json>\n\n. Parse each event as JSON and dispatch by type:
Event shape
Meaning
Frontend action
{"type": "meta", "thread_id": "..."}
Start of stream; save thread_id for follow-ups
Save thread_id to component state
{"type": "chunk", "text": "..."}
A chunk of the AI's response text
Append to the current AI message in the display
{"type": "form", "spec": {...}}
Render a form widget inline
Render the form (existing form widget code)
{"error": "..."}
Server-side error
Show as a system message: "Error: "
[DONE] (raw, not JSON)
Stream end
Finalize the current AI message
Task E — Handle HTTP error responses
On /api/v1/chat/stream, before the SSE starts:
HTTP 400: malformed request or unknown module. Show error toast.
HTTP 403: user has no access to this module. Show: "You don't have access to this module. Please contact your administrator." Refresh the access_tree from /api/v1/auth/me/access since their permissions may have changed.
HTTP 401: token expired. Redirect to login.
Task F — Refresh access_tree on app load
On app initialization (or React mount), call GET /api/v1/auth/me/access with the stored token. Update localStorage with the fresh access_tree. This handles the case where an admin changed the user's permissions during the session.
