Chat scaffolding caveat
The chat endpoint accepts requests and responds with HTTP 200, BUT the AI workflow that generates the actual response is still being rebuilt on the backend. Until further notice, when you send a chat message, expect:
Stream starts with a meta event containing thread_id. ✓ (proves the endpoint is reachable)
No chunk events with AI text. (workflow doesn't produce output yet)
Stream ends with [DONE].
This is NOT a frontend bug. The chat UI should display "Working on it..." or a typing indicator during the silence and gracefully handle the empty response. Backend will start producing real AI responses after Tasks 4.2, 4.3, 4.4 complete.
When real chat output ships, you'll see chunk events flowing — no frontend code change needed if you've built Task D correctly.
